28. prope vera, ‘pretty nearly true ' : cf. 1. 6. 1.

30. arta toga, ‘ a toga of little breadth.' The toga was of an oval form, and folded, as a rule, along the greater axis of the ellipse. Hence in wearing it the breadth would be measured from the shoulders downwards ; and a toga, if too broad, would either trail or have to be arranged in elaborate folds. For a trailing toga as a sign of conceit cf. Epod. 4. 8. comitemzclientem. 31. Eutrapelus, a name given to P.
